Zagallo Calls Seven Overseas Players for Gold Cup 
Brazilian coach Mario Zagallo called up seven overseas-based players
for the team's CONCACAF Gold Cup, but FIFA player of the year Ronaldo
was left off the roster.
Zagallo recalled Edmundo of Italy's Fiorentina who was dropped off the
national team several months ago and called defenders Doriva of
Portugal's Porto and Ze Maria of Italy's Parma, midfielders Emerson of
Germany's Bayer Leverkussen, Elber of Bayern Munich, and Mauro Silva
and Flavio Conceicao of Spain's Deportivo de La Coruna for the games.
Brazil's first-round games is in Miami on Feburary 3.
